  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Project to support prevention and response to lifesaving and psychosocial wellbeing of children and adolescents affected by the conflict in Borno, Yobe and Adamawa</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Plan International will implement a 12 month child protection prevention and response programme to improve access to quality lifesaving services to ensure the protection of children. Interventions will focus on identification and services provision for children at risk of violence, exploitation, neglect and abuse including case management using CPIMS+ for former CAAG and children with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
